Participants will explore current research to learn to recognize traits and types of perfectionistic behaviors while evaluating the impact of perfectionism on the lives of students both in and out of school. Participants will learn the relationships among perfectionism, procrastination and underachievement and consider the role introversion plays in the psychological mixture.  Methods for helping students use their perfectionist tendencies in positive ways will be explored and practical application expressed through projects and activities.








 
